    "analysis": "From prior steps we narrowed candidates to service-level faults across many services (widespread socket anomalies) and a prominent disk I/O spike on recommendationservice (highest severity_ratio ≈ 2.26). Trace aggregates show a traffic/row_count surge reaching P95 across many services, including root→recommendationservice row_count. According to the localization rules, the root cause should be a faulty service (from the provided candidate list) that is the most downstream faulty service in the trace call chain and shows a significant deviation from thresholds. Recommendationservice is both (a) flagged by metrics with the highest severity (diskio) and (b) appears in traces as a target of root→recommendationservice row_count anomalies. To confirm recommendationservice as the root cause, we must verify that recommendationservice trace series (duration / row_count / error_rate) show anomalies during the incident window and that other candidate services are not the more downstream faulty services in the same call chains.",
